<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><a name="Item1_03"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Item 1.03</font></u></b></a><b><u><font style="font-weight:bold;">.&#160; Bankruptcy or Receivership </font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On
December 20, 2004, the United States
Bankruptcy Court for the District of Arizona in Phoenix, Arizona (the &#147;Bankruptcy
Court&#148;), confirmed our joint Chapter 11 plan (the &#147;Plan&#148;) as filed by the Plan
proponents.&#160; The Plan is a liquidating
plan and includes the transfer of our timberlands and certain assets to a new
entity (or entities), that will be owned by the creditors that hold liens in the
timberlands.&#160; The Plan also provides for
the substantive consolidation of the entities included in our consolidated
group (the &#147;Debtors&#148;) and the creation of a liquidating trust that will dispose
of the remaining assets of the Debtors and disburse the proceeds thereof to
creditors in accordance with the Plan. &#160;The Plan proponents presently intend that the effective
date of the Plan will be December 31, 2004.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In addition, the Plan provides that on the effective
date of the Plan Crown Pacific Partners, L.P. will be dissolved and all 30,527,030
outstanding common units of Crown Pacific Partners, L.P. will be canceled with
no payment to the unitholders.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<h1 style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;page-break-after:auto;text-decoration:underline;"><a name="Item9_01"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Item
9.01</font></u></b></a><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">.&#160; Financial Statements and Exhibits</font></b></h1>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(c)
Exhibits</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The
following exhibits are filed herewith and this list is intended to constitute
the exhibit index:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="border-collapse:collapse;width:100.0%;">

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">CP Acquisition Company, an Oregon corporation, Crown Pacific Limited
Partnership, a Delaware limited partnership (&#147;<u>CPLP</u>&#148;), Crown Pacific
Partners, L.P., a Delaware limited partnership (&#147;<u>CPP</u>&#148;), CP Air, Inc., an
Oregon corporation, CP Acquisition II Co., an Oregon corporation, and CP
Acquisition III Co., an Oregon corporation, each a debtor and
debtor-in-possession in the above-captioned Chapter 11 cases (collectively, the
&#147;<u>Debtors</u>&#148;), together with the Noteholder Proponents (as defined herein),
the Bank Term Lender Proponents (as defined herein), and the Creditors&#146;
Committee (as defined herein) propose the following Second Amended Joint
Consolidating Chapter 11 Plan, dated as of December 20, 2004, pursuant to
section 1121(c) of the Bankruptcy Code.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">DISCLAIMER </font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">The Disclosure Statement accompanying this Plan, including the exhibits
appended thereto, provides information about the Debtors&#146; business, results of
operations and properties, and includes a summary and detailed analysis of this
Plan. All Creditors are encouraged to consult the Disclosure Statement and to
read this Plan carefully and completely before voting to accept or reject this
Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">NO
SOLICITATION MATERIALS, OTHER THAN THIS PLAN, THE ACCOMPANYING DISCLOSURE STATEMENT
AND EXHIBITS APPENDED THERETO AS APPROVED BY THE BANKRUPTCY COURT HAVE BEEN
AUTHORIZED BY THE COURT FOR USE IN SOLICITING ACCEPTANCES OR REJECTIONS OF THIS
PLAN.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><a name="ArticleIDefinitionsAndRulesOfInter"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE I<br>
<br>
</font></b></a><b><u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">DEFINITIONS AND RULES OF INTERPRETATION</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">For the purposes of this Plan, the following terms (which appear herein
as capitalized terms) have the respective meanings as hereinafter set forth;
such meanings are equally applicable to the singular and the plural forms of
the terms defined, unless the context otherwise</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">1</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

</div>
<!-- SEQ.=1,FOLIO='1',FILE='C:\JMS\ctaft\04-15059-1\task259415\15059-1-kc-01.htm',USER='ctaft',CD='Dec 21 11:34 2004' -->


<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">requires.
Capitalized terms used in this Plan at all times refer to terms defined in this
Article I. Unless otherwise provided in this Plan, all terms used herein have
the meaning assigned to them under title 11 of the United States Code (as
amended from time to time, the &#147;<u>Bankruptcy Code</u>&#148;) or the Federal Rules
of Bankruptcy Procedure (as amended from time to time, the &#147;<u>Bankruptcy Rules</u>&#148;).
The rules of construction applicable to the Bankruptcy Code and the Bankruptcy
Rules are applicable to this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:1.0in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Abandoned
Assets</u>&#148; means the Assets to be abandoned by the Debtors which shall be
listed on Schedule 5.2.2, and for which abandonment is approved by Final Order.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Administrative
Expense Claim</u>&#148; means a Claim to the extent that it is of the kind described
in section 503(b) of the Bankruptcy Code and is entitled to priority under
section 507(a)(1) of the Bankruptcy Code, together with any Fee Claim.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.3&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Administrative
Reserve</u>&#148; means the reserve established and maintained pursuant to section
6.6.1 of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.4&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Affiliate</u>&#148;
has the meaning set forth in section 101 of the Bankruptcy Code.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.5&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Aggregate
Allowed Class 4 Claims</u>&#148; means the aggregate amount of Allowed Class 4
Claims after all Disputed Class 4 Claims have been resolved.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.6&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Allowed</u>&#148;
means, with reference to any Claim (or portion thereof) or Interest and with
respect to each Debtor: (a) any Claim against or Interest in such Debtor that
has been listed by the Debtor in its Bankruptcy Schedules, as liquidated in
amount and not Disputed or contingent and for which no contrary proof of claim
or interest has been filed; or (b) as to which a proof of claim or application
has been timely filed in a liquidated amount with the Court pursuant to the
Bankruptcy Code or any order of the Court, or late filed with leave of the
Court after notice and a hearing, <i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided </font></i>that
(i) no objection to the allowance of a Claim under clause (a) or (b) above, or
motion to expunge such Claim, has been interposed before any final date for the
filing of such</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">objections or motions set forth
in this Plan, the Confirmation Order or other order of the Court, or (ii) such
Claim or Interest is held allowed by Final Order; <i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided</font></i>, <i><font style="font-style:italic;">further</font></i>,
that any Claims or Interests allowed solely for the purpose of voting to accept
or reject this Plan pursuant to an order of the Court shall not be considered
&#147;Allowed Claims&#148; or &#147;Allowed Interests&#148; for the purpose of Distributions
hereunder.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.7&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Assets</u>&#148;
means, as to each of the Debtors, all of such Debtor&#146;s right, title and
interest as of the Effective Date in and to any and all assets, property,
interests (including equity interests) and effects, real and personal, tangible
and intangible, wherever situated.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.8&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bank
Loans</u>&#148; means the loans outstanding pursuant to the Bank Loan Documents.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.9&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bank
Loan Documents</u>&#148; means that (i) certain Amended and Restated Credit
Agreement dated as of December 1, 1999, among CPLP, each of Bank Term Lenders
and Bank of America, N.A., as the Bank Term Lender Agent, as amended by that
certain First Amendment to Amended and Restated Credit Agreement dated as of
April 20, 2001, by that certain Temporary Waiver to Amended and Restated Credit
Agreement dated as of September 28, 2001, by that certain Temporary Waiver to
Amended and Restated Credit Agreement dated as of November 1, 2001, by that
certain Second Amendment to Amended and Restated Credit Agreement dated as of
November 7, 2001 and by that certain Third Amendment to Amended and Restated
Credit Agreement dated as of April 19, 2002, (ii) certain Notes executed by
CPLP in favor of each of the Bank Term Loan Lenders evidencing CPLP&#146;s
obligation under the Amended and Restated Credit Agreement, and (iii) any other
documents delivered to the Bank Term Lender Agent or any Bank Term Lenders in
connection therewith.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.10&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bank
Term Lenders</u>&#148; means those Entities that are Creditors of CPLP pursuant to
the Bank Loan Documents.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">3</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.11&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bank
Term Lender Agent</u>&#148; means Bank of America N.A., as agent for the Bank Term
Lenders under and pursuant to the Bank Loan Documents, and any successors or
assigns thereto.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.12&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bank
Term Lender Proponents</u>&#148; means singularly and/or collectively the Bank Term
Lenders identified on Schedule 1.12 hereto and each other Bank Term Lender that
delivers to counsel for the Debtors on or before the date that is three (3)
Business Days before the Confirmation Hearing a written request to be a Bank
Term Lender Proponent.&#160; The Bank Term
Lender Proponents as of the filing date of this Plan are identified as Plan
Proponents on Schedule 1.12 to this Plan (which Schedule 1.12 may be amended to
include Bank Term Lenders who timely submit requests to become Bank Term Lender
Proponents).</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.13&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bankruptcy
Code</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in this Article I.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.14&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bankruptcy
Rules</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in this Article I.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.15&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bankruptcy
Schedules</u>&#148; means the schedules of assets and liabilities, the list of
holders of Interests and the statements of financial affairs filed by the
Debtors under section 521 of the Bankruptcy Code and Bankruptcy Rule 1007, and
all amendments and modifications thereto through the Confirmation Date.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.16&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Acceptance</u>&#148; means the affirmative vote of the Bonners Ferry Parties
of their Allowed Bonners Ferry Claims as may be required under the Bankruptcy
Code for Class 7 acceptance of the treatment of such Allowed Bonners Ferry
Claims set forth in section 4.2.7.1(a).</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.17&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Assets</u>&#148; means CPLP&#146;s rights and interests in the Bonners Ferry
Facility Lease, the Bonners Ferry Site Lease, the L-P Sublease and the L-P
Purchase Agreement.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.18&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Claims</u>&#148; means any Unsecured Claim of a Bonners Ferry Party and/or LPC
under any of the Bonners Ferry Documents.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.19&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Consensual Transaction Acceptance</u>&#148; means the affirmative vote of (i)
LPC of its Allowed Claims and (ii) the Bonners Ferry Parties of their Allowed
Bonners Ferry Claims as may be required under the Bankruptcy Code for (x)
acceptance by LPC of the treatment of its Allowed Claims set forth in section
4.2.7.1(b) of this Plan and (y) acceptance by the Bonners Ferry Parties of
their Allowed Bonners Ferry Claims set forth in Section 4.2.7.1(b).</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.20&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Documents</u>&#148; means the Participation Agreement, Tax Indemnity
Agreement, the Bonners Ferry Site Lease, Bonners Ferry Facility Lease, LPC
Purchase Agreement, LPC Sublease, Bonners Ferry Sublease Assignment, Bonners
Ferry Security Interest, and all other documents and agreements delivered in
connection therewith.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.21&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Facility Lease</u>&#148; means the Facility Lease (Idaho) dated November 18,
1988, between the Owner-Trustee, as lessor, and CPLP, as lessee.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.22&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Party</u>&#148; means any Person that is a party to a Bonners Ferry Document
or any other Person that asserts a Claim against the Debtors pursuant to a
Bonners Ferry Document, but specifically excluding LPC and the Debtors.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.23&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Realty</u>&#148; means the real property in the State of Idaho on which the
Bonners Ferry sawmill is located, a legal description of which is attached to
the Bonners Ferry Site Lease.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.24&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Bonners
Ferry Security Interest</u>&#148; means the Deed of Trust, dated as of October 15,
1998, from the Owner Trustee to the Chicago Title Insurance Company for the
benefit of the Indenture Trustee, and any other documentation perfecting any
security interest granted by ICX Corporation to or for the benefit of the Indenture
Trustee in the Bonners Ferry Realty and certain personal property at the
Bonners Ferry sawmill site.</p>

closed under the laws applicable in the State of Arizona.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.28&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Cash</u>&#148;

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.29&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Cause
of Action</u>&#148; means any claim or cause of action, legal or equitable, now
owned or hereafter acquired by the Debtors, whether arising under any contract
or federal or state law, including but not limited to fraudulent conveyance
actions and any causes of action arising under section 506, 510, 542, 543, 544,
545, 546, 547, 548, 549, 550, 551 or 553(b) of the Bankruptcy Code, whether
commenced prior or subsequent to the Petition Date.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

11</u>&#148; means Chapter 11 of the Bankruptcy Code.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.34&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class</u>&#148;

this Plan.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.35&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class

of Distributable Cash; plus</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">(ii) the Class 5 Funded Amount;

Class 4 Sharing Percentage of the Value of NewCo Ancillary Assets; plus</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">(iv) the Class 4 Sharing Percentage
of the NewCo Corp Funding Amount. <i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided</font></i>,
<i><font style="font-style:italic;">however</font></i>, that in no event shall
the Class 4 Aggregate Distribution be greater than the Aggregate Allowed Class

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.36&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class
4 Received Percentage</u>&#148; means the quotient, expressed as a percentage, of (a)
aggregate amount of Distributions received by the holders of Allowed Class 4
Claims to (b) Aggregate Allowed Class 4 Claims.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.37&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class
4 Sharing Percentage</u>&#148; means the quotient, expressed as a percentage, of (a)
Aggregate Allowed Class 4 Claims to (b) the sum of (i) Aggregate Allowed Class
4 Claims and (ii) Aggregate Allowed Class 5 Claims.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.38&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class
5 Funded Amount</u>&#148; means $1,000,000.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.39&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Class
5 Sharing Percentage</u>&#148; means the quotient, expressed as a percentage, of (a)
Aggregate Allowed Class 5 Claims to (b) the sum of (i) Aggregate Allowed Class
4 Claims and (ii) Aggregate Allowed Class 5 Claims.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.40&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Collateral</u>&#148;
means any property or interest in property of the Estates subject to a Lien or
Security Interest to secure the payment or performance of a Claim, which Lien
or Security Interest is not subject to avoidance under the Bankruptcy Code or
otherwise invalid under the Bankruptcy Code or applicable non-bankruptcy law.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.41&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Collateral
Agent</u>&#148; means the Bank of America, N.A., as collateral agent to the Term
Lenders pursuant to the Intercreditor Agreement.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.42&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Committee
Consent</u>&#148; means, as to any action or issue requiring consent of the
Creditors&#146; Committee under this Plan, the consent or acceptance of a simple

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.43&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Confirmation
Date</u>&#148; means the date upon which the clerk of the Court enters the
Confirmation Order.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.44&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Confirmation

this Plan pursuant to section 1129 of the Bankruptcy Code, as such hearing may
be adjourned or continued from time to time.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.45&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Confirmation
Order</u>&#148; means the order entered by the Court confirming this Plan in
accordance with the Bankruptcy Code.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.46&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Consolidated
Estate</u>&#148; means the Estates of the Debtors as substantively consolidated
pursuant to Article II of this Plan.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.47&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Court</u>&#148;
means the United States Bankruptcy Court for the District of Arizona, or such
other Court as may from time to time have jurisdiction over the Chapter 11
Cases.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.48&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>CP
Admin Group</u>&#148; means, individually and/or collectively, CPALP, SVE II, LLC
(f/k/a SVE II, Inc.), Deborah L. Duncan, James A. Bondoux, Robert Jaunich II,
Peter W. Stott, Roger L. Krage, Crown Pacific, Ltd., SK Partners, HS Corp. of
Oregon, SK Timber Company, LLC, StoKra LLC, Fremont Investors, Inc. (f/k/a
Fremont Group, Inc.), Fremont Sequoia Holdings, L.P., Sequoia Ventures Inc.,
Sequoia Ventures Holdings, L.P., Fremont Euro-Summit Limited, Fremont Timber,
Inc., FTI Holdings, L.P., Fremont Group, L.L.C., SVE, Inc., Columbia
Investments II LLC and the Jaunich Living Trust U/A6/22/71 dated June 22, 1971.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.53&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Creditor</u>&#148;

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.54&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Creditors&#146;

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.55&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Cure</u>&#148;
means the distribution of Cash, or such other property, relief or arrangement
as may be agreed upon by the parties or ordered by the Court, with respect to
the assumption of an executory contract or unexpired lease, pursuant to section
365(b) of the Bankruptcy Code.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Bank Term Lender Proponents
dated November 10, 2004, as the same may be amended or supplemented.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.60&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Disputed</u>&#148;
means the portion (including, when appropriate, the whole) of any Claim as to
which: (a) a proof of claim or application has been or been deemed timely and
properly filed under applicable law or by a Final Order; (b) an objection,
motion to estimate, or complaint to determine the validity, priority or extent
of any Lien asserted by the claimant with respect to the Claim has been timely
filed; and (c) such objection, motion or complaint has not been withdrawn or
granted, denied or otherwise determined by Final Order.&#160; Before the time that such an objection,
motion or complaint has been filed, a Claim shall be considered Disputed (w) to
the extent, if any, that the amount of the Claim specified in a proof of claim
exceeds the amount of any corresponding Claim scheduled by the Debtors in their
Bankruptcy Schedules; (x) in its entirety, if any corresponding Claim scheduled
by the Debtors has been scheduled as disputed, contingent or unliquidated in the
Bankruptcy Schedules; (y) in its entirety, if any corresponding Claim scheduled
by the Debtors in their Bankruptcy Schedules places the Claim in a separate
classification from that asserted in a proof of claim; or (z) in its entirety,
if no corresponding Claim has been scheduled by the Debtors in their Bankruptcy
Schedules.&#160; In addition, &#147;Disputed&#148;
means, with respect to any Claim scheduled by the Debtors but not scheduled as
disputed, contingent or unliquidated, and as to which no corresponding proof of
claim was filed, the portion (including, when appropriate, the whole) of the
Claim as to which the Liquidating Trustee has made (or has assumed the pursuit
of) an objection in accordance with this Plan.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.61&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Disputed
Claims Reserve</u>&#148; means the reserve established and maintained by the
Liquidating Trustee pursuant to section 6.6.2 of this Plan.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.62&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Distributable

Trust at any given time after payment in full of or adequate reservation for:
(i) all</p>

Loan Documents and Senior Notes must be listed in CPLP&#146;s records for purposes
of transfers to be made under this Plan on the Effective Date, which shall be
the third Business Day immediately following the Confirmation Date at 5:00 p.m.
prevailing Pacific time.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

Date</u>&#148; means the first Business Day following the day on which the
conditions specified in section 13.1 of this Plan have been satisfied in full,
and which shall be identified in a notice filed and served pursuant to section
14.3 of this Plan.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.67&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Entity</u>&#148;
has the meaning as set forth in section 101(15) of the Bankruptcy Code.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.68&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Estates</u>&#148;
means, collectively, the estate for each of the Debtors that was created by the
commencement of the Chapter 11 Cases pursuant to section 541 of the Bankruptcy
Code, and shall be deemed to include, without limitation, any and all
privileges of the Debtors and any and all interests in property, whether real,
personal or mixed, rights, causes of action, avoidance powers or extensions of
time that the Debtors or the estate shall have had effective as of the Petition
Date or thereafter, whether by virtue of section 544, 545, 546, 547, 548, 549
or 550 of the Bankruptcy Code or otherwise.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.74&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Final

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.77&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Final
Order</u>&#148; means an order of the Court as to which the time to appeal, petition
for certiorari, or move for re-argument or rehearing has expired and as to
which no appeal, petition for certiorari, or other proceedings for re-argument
or rehearing shall then be pending or as to which any right to appeal, petition
for certiorari, reargue, or rehear shall have been waived in writing in form
and substance satisfactory to the Proponents or, in the event that an appeal,
writ of certiorari, or re-argument or rehearing thereof has been sought, such
order of the Court on the last</p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">such
appeal shall have been determined by the highest court to which such order was
appealed with no further remand or other proceedings contemplated, or
certiorari, re-argument or rehearing shall have been denied and the time to
take any further appeal, petition for certiorari, or move for re-argument or
rehearing shall have expired; <i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided</font></i>,
<i><font style="font-style:italic;">however</font></i>, that the possibility
that a motion under Rule 59 or Rule 60 of the Federal Rules of Civil Procedure,
or Rule 9023 or Rule 9024 of the Bankruptcy Rules, may be filed with respect to
such order shall not cause such order not to be a Final Order.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.78&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>401(k)
Plan</u>&#148; means the Crown Pacific Profit Sharing and Employee Savings Benefit
Plan sponsored by CPLP.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.79&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Foxglove
Option</u>&#148; means the option granted pursuant to the Foxglove Option Agreement.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.80&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Foxglove
Option Agreement</u>&#148; means the Option to Purchase Real Property, made as of
October 15, 1997, by and between CPLP and Foxglove L.L.C., a Washington limited
liability company.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.81&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Foxglove

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.82&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>General
Unsecured Claim</u>&#148; means any Unsecured Claim other than a Term Lender

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.83&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Glen

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.107&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Corp</u>&#148; means a corporation or corporations formed under the laws of the
State of Delaware that will be organized prior to the Effective Date in
accordance with this Plan and the entire equity ownership of which shall be
assigned to the respective Term Lender that requested that it receive NewCo
Corp Shares in accordance with this Plan.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.108&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Corp Funding Amount</u>&#148; means an amount of Cash equal to one percent of the
aggregate value of the Assets transferred to NewCo and the NewCo Subsidiaries
pursuant to this Plan, without duplication, on the Effective Date, <i><font style="font-style:italic;">i.e. </font></i>$3,091,638.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.109&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Corp Shares</u>&#148; means the uncertificated equity ownership shares of common
stock issued by each NewCo Corp.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.110&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Entities</u>&#148; means, collectively, NewCo, each NewCo Corp and each NewCo
Subsidiary.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.111&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Membership Interests</u>&#148; means the uncertificated membership interests issued
by NewCo.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.112&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Subsidiary</u>&#148; means each single member limited liability company formed under
the laws of the State of Delaware that will be established prior to the
Effective Date in accordance with this Plan and the equity ownership of which
shall be held by NewCo in accordance with this Plan.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.113&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>NewCo
Unit</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in Section 4.2.2.2 of this Plan.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.114&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Non-Insider</u>&#148;
means an Entity that is not an Insider.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.115&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Non-Insider
Preference Claim</u>&#148; shall mean a Preference Claim against any Non-Insider,
which are released under this Plan.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.116&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Noteholder</u>&#148;
means any Holder of a Senior Note.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">real
property Collateral is located and (ii) not subordinate or junior to the lien
of the Collateral Agent.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.133</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Priority
Tax Claim</u>&#148; means any Claim of a governmental unit of the kind specified in
section 502(i) or section 507(a)(8) of the Bankruptcy Code. Priority Tax Claims
do not include <i><font style="font-style:italic;">ad valorem </font></i>tax
claims if such Claims under applicable state law are secured by a Lien on any
of the Debtors&#146; Assets.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.134</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<i><u><font style="font-style:italic;">Pro Rata</font></u></i>&#148; means a proportionate
sharing, so that the ratio of the consideration distributed on account of an
Allowed Claim in a Class to the amount that such Allowed Claim is the same as
the ratio of the amount of the consideration distributed on account of all
Allowed Claims in such Class to the amount of all Allowed Claims in such Class.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.135</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Professional</u>&#148;
means a professional Entity retained (i) prior to the Effective Date by the
Debtors or the Creditors&#146; Committee with Court approval, or (ii) subsequent to
the Effective Date, by the Liquidating Trustee or Creditors&#146; Committee or the
Required Proponent Term Lenders in accordance with the terms of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.136</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Proponents</u>&#148;
means, singularly and/or collectively, each of the Debtors, Proponent Term
Lenders and the Creditors&#146; Committee, as co-proponents of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.137</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Proponent
Term Lenders</u>&#148; means (i) on or prior to the Effective Date, each of the Bank
Term Lender Proponents and the Noteholder Proponents; and (ii) after the

determination.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.138</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released
Committee Claims</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in section 8.8.1.</font></p>

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt .5in;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.140</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released CP

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.141</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>&#147;<u>Released Debtor Affiliates</u>&#148;
means individually and/or collectively, (i) CPM and (ii) any Entity that holds
an equity interest in CPM (but excluding any Entity that is within the CP Admin
Group).</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.142</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released
Debtor Persons</u>&#148; means Deborah L. Duncan, Richard B. Keller, Lee C. Simpson,
Mark V. Allred, Gary N. Cremer, Steven E. Dietrich, John S. Ernst, P. A.
(&#147;Tony&#148;) Leineweber, Susan R. Steers, Brandon L. Works, L. James Weeks, Richard
D. Snyder, Christopher Mumford, William L. Smith, Charles E. Carlbom, John W.
Larson, and James A. Bondoux, except to the extent any such Person receives a
release pursuant to this Plan as a member of the CP Admin Group.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.143</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released
Debtor Persons&#146; Claims</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in section 8.9.1.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.144</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released
Lender Parties</u>&#148; means, collectively, the Collateral Agent, the Bank Term
Lender Agent, the Term Lenders, and each of their respective past, current and
future members, shareholders, directors, officers, employees, agents,
accountants, financial advisors, attorneys, trustees, representatives, other
affiliates and their successors and assigns.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.145</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Released
Term Lender Claims</u>&#148; has the meaning set forth in section 8.6.1.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.146</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Required
Class 5 Holders</u>&#148; means, after the Effective Date, any composition of
Holders holding in excess of fifty percent (50%) of the aggregate amount of
Allowed Class 5 Claims.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.147</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Required
Proponent Term Lenders</u>&#148; means (i) on or prior to the Effective Date, as of
any date of determination, any composition of the Proponent Term Lenders that
held at least two-thirds (2/3s) of the aggregate Proponent Term Lender Claims;
and (ii) after the Effective Date, as of any date of determination, the
Required Class 5 Holders.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.150</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Secured
Claim</u>&#148; means any Claim, to the extent reflected in the Bankruptcy Schedules
or a proof of claim as a Secured Claim, to the extent it is secured by a valid,
unavoidable Lien or Security Interest in Collateral (whether consensual or otherwise),
to the extent of the value of the Estates&#146; interest in such Collateral, as
determined in accordance with section 506(a) of the Bankruptcy Code and taking
into account any other Secured Claims with respect to such Collateral not
inferior in priority to such Secured Claim, or, in the event that such Claim is
subject to setoff under section 553 of the Bankruptcy Code, to the extent of
such setoff.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.151</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Secured Tax

law is secured by a Lien on any of the Debtors&#146; Assets.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.152</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Security

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Made
Pursuant to the Terms Thereunder Without Further Order of the Court entered on
May 19, 2004.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.155</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Subordinated
Claim</u>&#148; means any Claim that is subordinated by Final Order pursuant to
section 510 of the Bankruptcy Code or otherwise.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.156</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;</font><u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Tax Indemnity Agreement</font></u><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#148; means the Tax Indemnity
Agreement, dated as of October 30, 1998, between CPLP and ICX Corporation.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.157</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term Lender
Claim</u>&#148; means a Claim against the Debtors arising under or pursuant to a
Senior Note and/or the Bank Loan Documents.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.158</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term Lender
Collateral</u>&#148; means the Collateral securing the Term Lender Claims.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.159</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term Lender
Consent</u></font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#148;</font><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;"> means, as to
any action or issue requiring consent of the Term Lenders under this Plan, the
consent or acceptance (in accordance with section 14.5 of this Plan) of the
Required Proponent Term Lenders.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.160</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term Lender
Deficiency Claim</u>&#148; means the Unsecured portion of a Term Lender Claim in
accordance with section 506(a) of the Bankruptcy Code.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.161</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term Lender
Secured Claim</u>&#148; means that portion of a Term Lender Claim that is secured by
the Term Lender Collateral.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.162</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Term
Lenders</u>&#148; means, singularly and/or collectively, each of the Bank Term
Lenders, the Bank Term Lender Agent, the Collateral Agent and the Noteholders.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.163</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Trust
Assets</u>&#148; means all Assets except (i) the Term Lender Collateral (provided that
the Excluded Collateral listed on Schedule 5.2.1 as transferred to the Trust
shall constitute Trust Assets), (ii) the Abandoned Assets, (iii) the Bonners
Ferry Assets (other than the LPC Escrow) and Bonners Ferry Realty if Bonners
Ferry Acceptance or Bonners Ferry Consensual Transaction Acceptance is
received, (vi) the NewCo Ancillary Assets, (v) the NewCo Corp</font></p>

Amount, and (vi) equity interests in the NewCo Entities and the Assets
transferred to the NewCo Entities in accordance with this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.164</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Trust

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.165</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Unclassified

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">1.166</font></b><b><font size="1" style="font-size:3.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&#147;<u>Unsecured
