<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">11.1.17&#160; </font></b>to enter a Final Decree and any other order
necessary to, or in furtherance of, the closure of the Chapter 11 Cases; and</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">11.1.18&#160; </font></b>to enter any order necessary or appropriate
to effect, interpret, clarify or enforce the provisions of this Plan.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">11.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="JurisdictionUnaffe"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Jurisdiction Unaffe</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">cted. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">The occurrence of
the Effective Date and/or the entry of a Final Decree shall not divest the
Court of any jurisdiction otherwise retained under this Article 11 or the
Confirmation Order.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><a name="ArticleXii"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE XII</font></b></a></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">CERTAIN
OBLIGATIONS OF THE DEBTORS</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="ObligationsForThePer"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Obligations for
the Per</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">iod Between the
Confirmation Date and the Effective Date. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Between the Confirmation Date and the
Effective Date, the Debtors, in addition to performance of their other
obligations as may be required hereunder or under the Bankruptcy Code and prior
orders of the Court, shall:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1.1 </font></b>take such legal and authorized actions and execute such documents as
may be reasonably requested in writing by the Creditors&#146; Committee and/or the
Proponent Term Lenders to consummate this Plan;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1.2 </font></b>continue to maintain insurance on all assets of the Estates in
accordance with ordinary course practices, except as expressly permitted by
Term Lender Consent and Committee Consent;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1.3 </font></b>maintain all of their books, records and accounting systems in
accordance wit h their past practices, or altered only with Proponent Term
Lender Consent;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1.4 </font></b>not sell or dispose of any assets of the Estates, or any proceeds
thereof, except (i) in the ordinary course of business operations, (ii) as
contemplated by this Plan, (iii)</p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">85</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">with
Committee Consent and/or Term Lender Consent (in each instance as the case may
be pursuant to the terms of this Plan), or (iv) otherwise as may be authorized
by order of the Court; and</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt 12.0pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.1.5 </font></b>commence actions to terminate the 401(k) Plan, including requesting
that the 401(k) Plan administrator take any actions necessary to effectuate
such termination and to cause a complete distribution of the 401(k) Plan assets
as soon as reasonably practicable.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">12.2&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="ObligationsAsOfTheEffe"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Obligations as
of the Effe</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">ctive Date. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Each of the
Debtors&#146; remaining officers, directors and general partners shall be deemed to
have resigned and/or withdrawn as of the Effective Date, and such Persons
(together with the members of the Board of Control of CPM, the officers of CPM,
and any general partners of the Debtors&#146; general partners) shall as of that
date have no further duties, responsibilities or obligations as officers,
directors, general partners or otherwise to the Debtors, the Estates, any
Creditors or Interest holders, and all such parties shall be deemed to have
consented to such resignations and/or withdrawals, <i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided, however</font></i>, that if specifically authorized and
requested by the Liquidating Trustee (acting in its capacity as Estate
Representative), one or more officers of the Debtors may execute documents as
necessary or required to report on actions taken by or at the direction of the
Debtors, including with respect to termination of the 401(k) Plan. Each of the
Debtors&#146; Professionals, including lawyers and financial advisors, shall
conclude their engagements by and on behalf of the Debtors on the Effective
Date, and shall as of that date have no further duties, responsibilities or
obligations to the Debtors, the Estates, any Creditors or any Interest holders,
<i><font style="font-style:italic;">provided, however</font></i>, that the
Debtors&#146; Professionals and Debtor Released Persons, for agreed compensation,
shall assist the Liquidating Trustee or any NewCo Entity if such assistance is
reasonably requested, including assistance in connection with litigation in
which their knowledge of the Debtors&#146; operations and Assets may be relevant.
The deemed resignations and withdrawals provided for in this Section concern
solely the affected Persons&#146; duties, responsibilities and obligations as
officers, directors</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">86</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">or general
partners of any of the Debtors. Nothing in this Section shall be deemed to
determine the affected Persons &#145; employment status within the meaning of the
Retention Plan and Severance Program or their rights (if any) under the
Retention Plan and Severance Program.</font></p>

<p style="line-height:normal;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><a name="ArticleXiii"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE XIII</font></b></a></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">CONDITIONS
TO EFFECTIVE DATE</font></u></b></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="ConditionsToOc"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Conditions to Oc</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">currence of Effective Date. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Each of the following are conditions
precedent to the Effective Date, which conditions must be satisfied to the
reasonable satisfaction of the Proponents or waived, as applicable:</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>the Liquidating Trustee is willing to serve
in such capacity and the terms of its service and compensation as set forth in
the Liquidating Trust Agreement shall have been approved by the Court at the
Confirmation Hearing;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>the Liquidating Trust Agreement shall have
been executed and delivered by the Liquidating Trustee and any other parties
thereto;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.3&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>any outstanding fees of the U.S. Trustee
under 28 U.S.C. &#167; 1930 shall have been paid in full;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.4&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>the Confirmation Order shall have become a
Final Order, unless such condition shall have been waived by the Proponents;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.5&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>the Proponents shall have received all
authorizations, consents, regulatory approvals, rulings, letters, no-action
letters, opinions or documents that are reasonably determined by the Proponents
to be necessary to implement this Plan;</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.6&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>any real property included in the Abandoned
Assets, the Trust Assets and the Excluded Collateral shall have been
partitioned to establish such real property as separate</p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">87</font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">legal
lots to the extent required by local law, to the satisfaction of the Required
Proponent Term Lenders, unless waived by the Required Proponent Term Lenders;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.7&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>the NewCo Entities shall have been formed and
be duly existing, and shall be legally authorized (as applicable) to hold title
to the Assets that shall be transferred to the NewCo Entities under this Plan;
and</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:1.0in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">13.1.8&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; </font></b>action shall have been taken to terminate the
401(k) Plan, including the 401(k) Plan administrator having been requested to
take any actions necessary to effectuate such termination and to cause a
complete distribution of the 401(k) Plan assets as soon as reasonably
practicable.</p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><a name="ArticleXiv"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">ARTICLE XIV</font></b></a></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><b><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">MISCELLANEOUS PROVISIONS</font></u></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.1&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="NonconsensualConfi"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Nonconsensual Confi</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">rmation. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">As to any Class
that votes or is deemed to reject this Plan, the Proponents are seeking
confirmation of this Plan in accordance with section 1129(b) of the Bankruptcy
Code either under the terms provided herein or upon such terms as may exist if
this Plan is modified in accordance with section 1127(d) of the Bankruptcy
Code.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.2&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="Notic"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Notic</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">es. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Except as
otherwise set forth in section 14.4 below, all notices, requests, elections or
demands in connection with this Plan, including any change of address of any
Holder of a Claim for the purposes of receiving any Distributions under this
Plan, shall be in writing and shall be delivered personally or by telecopy,
e-mail or overnight delivery service, or mailed by stamped first class mail to
the Persons identified in this section. Such notice shall be deemed to have
been given the next Business Day after receipt or, if mailed by first class
mail, seven (7) days after the date of mailing:</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">88</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.3&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="NoticeOfEntryOfCo"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Notice of Entry of Co</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">nfirmation Order and Effective Date. </font></i></font></b>The Liquidating Trustee shall provide notice
by U.S. first class mail of the (i) entry of the Confirmation Order and (ii)
Effective Date, which may be contained in a single notice, to all parties
entitled to notice under Bankruptcy Rule 2002(f)(7) as soon as practicable
following the Effective Date. Such notice shall be deemed to be good and
sufficient notice of such matters, with no requirement for any additional or
further notice.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.4&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="FurtherNoticesPos"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Further Notices; Pos</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">t-Effective Date Service List.&#160; </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">From and after the
Effective Date, notices of appearance and demands for service of process filed
with the Court prior to such date shall no longer be effective. From and after
the Effective Date, no further notices, other than the Notice of Entry of the
Confirmation Order and the Notice of Effective Date of the Plan required by
section 14.3 of this Plan, shall be required to be sent to any Entity, except
each Entity that files with the Court a new notice of appearance and demand for
service dated subsequent to the Effective Date, which subsequent notice and
demand must be filed with the Court and served upon the Entities listed in
section 14.2.2.&#160; A list setting forth the
name, address, e-mail address (if any) and telephone number of each such Entity
shall be maintained by the Liquidating Trustee and shall be provided upon
request (the &#147;<u>Post-Effective Date Service List</u>&#148;).</font></p>

<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.5&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="NoticeForTermLenderCo"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Notice for Term Lender Co</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">nsent and Committee Consent. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">To the
extent any provision of this Plan or the Liquidating Trust Agreement requires
Term Lender Consent, the Entity seeking such consent shall direct the request
for consent to each Trust Beneficiary that holds Liquidating Trust interests in
respect of Allowed Class 5 Claims, and the Entity seeking such consent shall be
responsible for determining whether such consent has or has not been obtained,
and for notifying the Liquidating Trustee, the Proponent Term Lenders and the
Creditors&#146; Committee upon receipt of such consent, including acceptances and
rejections actually obtained. To the extent any provision of this Plan or the
Liquidating Trust Agreement requires Committee Consent, the Entity seeking such
consent shall be entitled to direct the request for approval to the Persons
designated in section 14.2 as Creditors&#146; Committee contacts, or such successors
thereto as shall be designated in filings with the Court and the Liquidating
Trustee, and those notified Committee contacts shall then be responsible for
determining whether such consent has or has not been obtained, and shall notify
the Liquidating Trustee, the Proponent Term Lenders and the Creditors&#146;
Committee upon receipt of such consent.&#160;
Any statement by the designated Person to any other Entity concerning
consent shall be dispositive.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.6&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="Headi"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Headi</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">ngs. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&#160;The headings used in this Plan are inserted
for convenience only and neither constitute a portion of this Plan nor in any
manner affect the provisions of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.7&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="Severabili"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Severabili</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">ty. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Should any provision in this Plan be
determined to be unenforceable, such determination shall in no way limit or
affect the enforceability and operative effect of any and all other provisions
of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.8&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="Computation"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Computation </font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">of Time. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">In computing any period of time
prescribed or allowed by this Plan, the provisions of Bankruptcy Rule 9006(a)
shall apply.</font></p>

<br clear="all" style="page-break-before:always;">


<div style="font-family:Times New Roman;">

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.9&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="GoverningL"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Governing L</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">aw. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Except to the extent that the
Bankruptcy Code or any other Federal law is applicable, the rights and
obligations arising under this Plan shall be governed by, and construed and
enforced in accordance with, the laws of the State of Arizona.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.10&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="SuccessorsAndA"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Successors and A</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">ssigns. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">The rights and
obligations of any Entity named or referred to in this Plan shall be binding
upon, and shall inure to the benefit of, the successors and assigns of such
Entity.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.11&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="CollateralAgentA"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Collateral Agent a</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">nd Administrative Agent Post-Effective Date
Role.&#160; </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">As a result
of the distributions, transfers and other treatments accorded to the Term
Lenders in connection with the Plan, the obligations and duties of Bank of
America, N.A., in its capacities as the Collateral Agent and the Bank Term
Lender Agent, shall terminate as of the Effective Date and, from and after such
date, Bank of America, N.A., shall have no further obligations or duties
arising in its capacities as the Bank Term Lender Agent or the Collateral Agent
to the Term Lenders or the Bank Term Lenders.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.12&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="Supersessi"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Supersessi</font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">on. </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">Except as otherwise specifically
provided for herein, in the event of any inconsistency between the terms of any
document and instrument prepared pursuant to this Plan or the Disclosure
Statement and the terms of this Plan (including without limitation, the
Liquidating Trust Agreement), the terms of this Plan shall govern and shall supersede
the terms of any such documents, instruments or Disclosure Statement. In the
event of any inconsistency between the terms of this Plan and the Confirmation
Order, the terms of the Confirmation Order shall govern and supersede the terms
of this Plan.</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="color:black;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;text-indent:.5in;"><b><font size="2" color="black" face="Times New Roman" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">14.13&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; <a name="IncorporationOfExhibits"><i><font style="font-style:italic;">Incorporation of Exhibits </font></i></a><i><font style="font-style:italic;">and Schedules; Plan Supplement and Supplement to
Schedules and Exhibits.&#160; </font></i></font></b><font size="2" color="black" style="color:windowtext;font-size:10.0pt;">All exhibits
and schedules referenced in this Plan are incorporated into this Plan in
full.&#160; Any supplement to this Plan filed
with the Court shall be incorporated into this Plan in full. From time to time
prior to the Confirmation Date, the Proponents with the approval of</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">94</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left">

</font></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1) This column includes
activity in CPLP&#146;s main funding account and accounts payable disbursement
accounts at Bank One listed on page 2a.&#160;
These accounts are all included in a centralized cash management system.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(2) This column includes
activity in CPLP&#146;s payroll accounts at Bank One listed on page 2a.&#160; The payroll accounts are all funded from the
main funding account.&#160; Activity includes
payroll paid to employees through Crown Pacific Management L.P., which is
charged to CPLP in a monthly management fee.&#160;
Amount includes gross payroll to employees as well as employer&#146;s taxes.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(3) This column represents
activity in CPLP&#146;s temporary cash investment account at Goldman Sachs.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(4) Includes rail car lease
revenue, rental revenue for cell towers, other revenue and misc. cash receipts
including collections made on behalf of accounts receivable sold to Interfor
with the manufacturing segment.&#160; Such
Interfor receipts were then remitted to Interfor by CPLP.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(5) Represents release of funds from escrow from the September 2004
sale of the manufacturing operations.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(6) Includes $500,000 in adequate protection payments.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">2</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(1)&#160; </font></b>CPLP was unable to
close its books for the Year 2003 until mid-April 2004 due to continuing
analysis with its external auditors regarding impairment issues for long-lived
assets as required under U.S. GAAP.&#160; In
April, 2004, subsequent to the submission of the December 2003 and January 2004
Monthly Operating Reports, several impairment charges were recorded to the
accounting period of December 2003 and additional adjustments were made to the
accounting period of January 2004.&#160; These
adjustments are further described on page 1a of the February 2004 MOR. The
effects of these out-of-period adjustments are included in the year to date
column in the 2004 MORs, and represent a timing difference between the 2004 MOR
reporting and CPLP&#146;s 2004 general ledger and SEC reporting.</p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(2)
</font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">&#160;</font></b>October 2004 non-cash charge
represents the write-off of CPLP&#146;s remaining deferred financing costs related
to the secured pre-petition debt.</p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left">

</font></div>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(1)</font></b> Certain officers responsible for the management of the debtor are
employees of Crown Pacific Management, L.P (&#147;CPM&#148;). The cost of their
compensation, along with other costs for non-officer headquarters employees and
certain other administrative costs, are initially incurred by CPM, and then
charged back to (CPLP) in the form of a monthly management fee.</p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">All officer compensation, whether paid by CPLP or CPM, is reported
above and throughout this MOR as officer compensation of the Debtor, with the
exception of payments made under the KERP and MSP order.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">(2) </font></b>Represents non-cash charge to write-off the remaining balance of
deferred financing costs, related to CPLP&#146;s secured pre-petition debt.</p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="1" width="25%" noshade color="black" align="left">

</font></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1) Represents gross salary
amounts and directors fees, before any deductions or withholdings.&#160; For confidentiality purposes, amounts in this
table do not include any payments that may have been made to one or more of the
individuals listed pursuant to the Court&#146;s Order Approving Debtors&#146; Key
Employee Retention Plan and Post-Petition Modified Severance Program and
Authorizing Payments to Be Made Pursuant to the Terms Therefunder Without
Further Order of the Court (the &#147;KERP and MSP Order&#148;).&#160; See note 2 on Page 3b for further discussion
of any payments made in the current period pursuant to the KERP and MSP order.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

  <td width="19%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:19.38%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.84%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="17%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:17.86%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="top" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.92%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="19%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:19.84%;">
  <p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
  <td width="1%" valign="bottom" bgcolor="#CCEEFF" style="background:#CCEEFF;padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:1.48%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">What steps have been taken
to remedy the problems which brought on the Chapter 11 filing?</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">A DIP Revolver was arranged
and fully implemented, new bank accounts and a cash management system were established.
The Debtors continue to work with their professionals and the creditors
regarding various restructuring options and have commenced a disposition
process with respect to certain assets.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In April 2004 CPLP closed the sale of its Las Vegas, Nevada operations
and applied the proceeds to the DIP Revolver loan.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In July 2004 CPLP closed the
sale of its Reno/Sparks, Nevada operations and paid off the remaining balance
of the DIP Revolver loan. The DIP Revolver loan agreement was terminated in
August 2004.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In August 2004 CPLP closed
the sale of its Arizona operations, thus completing the disposition of its
Alliance Lumber segment.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">In September 2004 CPLP
closed the sale of its manufacturing operations (sawmills) and short-line
railroad. $32,259,000 of the proceeds were paid to Bank of America, N.A.,
Collateral Agent. $16,243,484 of the proceeds were paid to extinguish a lease
obligation related to one of the sawmills. $833,050.09 of the proceeds were
paid to various taxing authorities.</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><u><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">Identify any matters that
are delaying the filing of a plan of reorganization:</font></u></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">On November 10, 2004, the
Bankruptcy Court approved the Disclosure Statement for the Second Amended Joint
Consolidating Chapter 11 Plan. A confirmation hearing with respect to the Plan
is scheduled for December 20, 2004.&#160; Work
continues between the debtors and representatives of the creditors on
transition planning for implementation of the proposed plan with a target
effective date of December 31, 2004.</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">7</font></p>

<div style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">

<hr size="2" width="100%" noshade color="gray" align="left">

</font></div>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">(1) Amount represents the difference between actual cash flows to CPM,
and the amount reported as CPM payroll cost. The CPM payroll cost is included
in the payroll disbursements figure. The difference flows into or out of the
CPM bank account.</font></p>

<p align="right" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:right;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;">CP
ACQUISITION III</font></p>

<p align="center" style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-align:center;text-autospace:none;"><font size="2" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">CP
Acquisition III</font></b></p>

<p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Balance
Sheet</font></b></p>

<p style="font-size:10.0pt;margin:0in 0in .0001pt;text-autospace:none;"><b><font size="2" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:10.0pt;font-weight:bold;">Accounting
Period Ending: </font></b><b><font style="font-weight:bold;">10/31/2004</font></b></p>

  <td width="82%" colspan="2" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:82.02%;">

  </td>
  <td width="2%" valign="bottom" style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in;width:2.3%;">
  <p style="margin:0in 0in .0001pt;"><b><font size="1" face="Times New Roman" style="font-size:1.0pt;font-weight:bold;">&nbsp;</font></b></p>
